==English==
===Adverb===
'''faithfully'''

#In a [[faithful]] manner.
#:''The CD reproduces music faithfully.''
#:''I have been faithully married for the past twenty years.''
#(''US'') A conventional [[formula]] for ending a [[letter]], used when the [[salutation]] addresses the person for whom the letter is intended using an [[honorific]].

====Synonyms====
*(''formula for ending correspondence''): [[yours faithfully]] (''UK'')<!--Note: "sincerely" is not a synonym as it is used differently-->

====Derived terms====
*[[yours faithfully]]

